<item>
            <title>[LU-1533] return the wrong size in ll_getxattr</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1533</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In ll_getxattr, &lt;br/&gt;
                 if (size == 0 &amp;amp;&amp;amp; S_ISDIR(inode-&amp;gt;i_mode)) {&lt;br/&gt;
                         /* XXX directory EA is fix for now, optimize to save&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;RPC transfer */&lt;br/&gt;
                        GOTO(out, rc = sizeof(struct lov_user_md));&lt;br/&gt;
when size == 0, it return the size of lov_user_md(lov_user_md_v1) as the LOV size. And if we set pool inside default EA, the return size would be less than the actual EA size(lov_user_md_v3). Then we will get error during rsync (with enable xattr).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
